# ─── Recommended: set these as real environment variables ───────────────────
# Pass them via your container orchestrator (docker compose `environment:`,
# k8s Secrets, systemd `Environment=`, fly secrets, etc.). Real env vars are
# the smaller, safer surface — no file on disk to mount, rotate, or leak.
#
# For local dev convenience only, you may copy this file to .env.local and
# fill it in (gitignored). npm start loads .env.local via
# --env-file-if-exists; real env vars always win over file values, so the
# two coexist cleanly when both are present.

# ─── Required ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# JWT secret for signing device-auth tokens. Any random ≥32-char string.
# Generate: openssl rand -base64 32
JWT_SECRET=

# Provider API key — only the selected provider's key needs to be set.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
# OPENAI_API_KEY=
# GEMINI_API_KEY=
# GROQ_API_KEY=
# MISTRAL_API_KEY=
# COHERE_API_KEY=
# PERPLEXITY_API_KEY=
# AI21_API_KEY=
# AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID= + AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY= + AWS_REGION=    # for bedrock

# ─── Local providers (OpenAI-compatible servers on this machine) ─────────────
# All three appear in the "Local" group of the provider picker. Override the
# baseURL only if you've moved a local server off its default port. The chat
# call surfaces a clear "Couldn't reach <Provider>" error if the server's not
# actually running.
# OLLAMA_BASE_URL=http://localhost:11434/v1
# LLAMACPP_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8080/v1
# LMSTUDIO_BASE_URL=http://localhost:1234/v1

# ─── Web search (Tavily) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Opt-in. When this key is set, the composer shows a 🌐 search toggle next to
# the model pill — flip it on and the active model can call Tavily as a tool
# during the response. Free tier: ~1000 calls/month at tavily.com.
# TAVILY_API_KEY=

# ─── Optional (defaults shown) ───────────────────────────────────────────────

# Which provider to use. One of: anthropic | openai | gemini | groq | mistral |
#                                 cohere | perplexity | bedrock | ai21 |
#                                 ollama | llamacpp | lmstudio
# CHATFRAME_PROVIDER=anthropic

# Provider-specific model ID. token.js's built-in list tops out at Claude
# 3.7-sonnet for Anthropic; the Claude 4.x family (Opus 4.7, Sonnet 4.6,
# Haiku 4.5) is registered explicitly via extendModelList in
# lib/server/ai-tools.ts. Add more models there as needed.
# CHATFRAME_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-6

# Baseline system prompt the model sees. Override to specialize the assistant.
# CHATFRAME_SYSTEM_PROMPT="You are a helpful AI assistant."
